{"id": "EUVD-2024-44746", "enisaUuid": "6df75c3f-bc22-33f4-be4c-3790259532a0", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\npinctrl: nuvoton: fix a double free in ma35_pinctrl_dt_node_to_map_func()\n\n'new_map' is allocated using devm_* which takes care of freeing the\nallocated data on device removal, call to\n\n\t.dt_free_map = pinconf_generic_dt_free_map\n\ndouble frees the map as pinconf_generic_dt_free_map() calls\npinctrl_utils_free_map().\n\nFix this by using kcalloc() instead of auto-managed devm_kcalloc().", "datePublished": "2024-10-29T00:50:12", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T20:27:21", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6441d9c3d71b59c8fd27d4e381c7471a32ac1a68", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3fd976afe9743110f20a23f93b7ff9693f2be4bf"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-50071"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.07, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "13dc643e-18ce-35ce-9787-aa26426d3dd6", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12"}, {"id": "2bdd75e8-9e1d-3a69-8a1b-8aaf4c5665e1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.11.5"}, {"id": "6941c9ab-9504-3d18-9bd6-fa44666e8389", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "98c4d5a4-d30a-35bb-9095-87beee52f293", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f805e356313bbcafef48808c14eb9ce7f4ff2560 <3fd976afe9743110f20a23f93b7ff9693f2be4bf"}, {"id": "e94e0e13-e05e-3526-884b-bbb49a389c15", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f805e356313bbcafef48808c14eb9ce7f4ff2560 <6441d9c3d71b59c8fd27d4e381c7471a32ac1a68"}, {"id": "ecda8d8b-b3ae-3ee2-a6f5-0a95ead57091", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.11"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "3564b8cb-f011-34db-ac9a-49a02a6ad345", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}